<title>|xue as ostrich and other things</title>
<summary>|xue becomes an ostrich and goes into a rock. He becomes an owl and dies and flies eat him. |xue&apos;s wife carries him to her house. She fetches a large pot and puts him in the pot, pours water on him and builds a great fire, intending to cook him. |xue cries because he is afraid of the fire and his wife asks if it is her husband who cries. |xue&apos;s wife breaks the pot and |xue says &apos;I say |xue&apos;, revealing himself. |xue&apos;s wife cries.</summary><comments>1) !nanni heard this from his paternal grandfather (Karu), 2) This story is found in Book XI &amp; XII-5</comments><date>March 1880</date><storypages>9349v-9353v</storypages><category>Transformation</category><author>!nanni (XI)</author><keyword><kw>|xue</kw><subkw>dies and is eaten by flies</subkw></keyword>
